This paper is primarily focused on the machine learning aspect of federated learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of distributed edge devices, which could fall under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the protection of data privacy, which could fall under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper's focus on generating datasets and evaluation metrics could also suggest that it belongs to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper's emphasis on real-world assumptions and open-source benchmarks could suggest that it belongs to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
